DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to set up two separate contexts using React's createContext: one for sharing the task state and one for the dispatch function. Both contexts have null as initial default values. This approach allows components to consume either the current state or the dispatch function as needed, and is fundamental for reducing prop-drilling in more complex React applications.
