TITLE: Defining a Standalone Reducer Function for Task Management (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Defines the `tasksReducer` function within its own module (`tasksReducer.js`). This pure function takes the current task list state and an action object, returning the new state based on the action type ('added', 'changed', 'deleted'). This separation improves code modularity and testability.
SOURCE: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/extracting-state-logic-into-a-reducer.md#2025-04-22_snippet_18

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
export default function tasksReducer(tasks, action) {
  switch (action.type) {
    case 'added': {
      return [
        ...tasks,
        {
          id: action.id,
          text: action.text,
          done: false,
        },
      ];
    }
    case 'changed': {
      return tasks.map((t) => {
        if (t.id === action.task.id) {
          return action.task;
        } else {
          return t;
        }
      });
    }
    case 'deleted': {
      return tasks.filter((t) => t.id !== action.id);
    }
    default: {
      throw Error('Unknown action: ' + action.type);
    }
  }
}
```

