TITLE: React Counter Component Using Parameterized useCounter Hook - React JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet displays a counter whose updating interval is controlled by a delay state (from a slider), which is passed as an argument to the useCounter Hook. The label and input range allow the user to dynamically adjust the tick duration between 10ms and 2000ms, ensuring the count updates in real-time. Requires useCounter to be implemented to accept and use the delay parameter.
SOURCE: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/reusing-logic-with-custom-hooks.md#2025-04-22_snippet_41

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import { useState } from 'react';
import { useCounter } from './useCounter.js';

export default function Counter() {
  const [delay, setDelay] = useState(1000);
  const count = useCounter(delay);
  return (
    <>
      <label>
        Tick duration: {delay} ms
        <br />
        <input
          type="range"
          value={delay}
          min="10"
          max="2000"
          onChange={e => setDelay(Number(e.target.value))}
        />
      </label>
      <hr />
      <h1>Ticks: {count}</h1>
    </>
  );
}
```

