TITLE: Submitting Form Data with Fetch in React - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet defines a React functional component that displays a form for editing a post, including a textarea for post content. On form submission, it prevents the default page reload, reads the form data using the FormData API, submits the data to an API endpoint via fetch, and logs the structured data to the console. Dependencies include React and browser FormData/fetch APIs. The main parameters are the form event and the form fields (postTitle, postContent), with inputs from the form and no explicit output except side effects (console and network requests).
