TITLE: Utility Functions with Artificially Slowed Filtering (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This file contains utility functions. `createTodos` generates an array of 50 todo objects. `filterTodos` filters this array based on the `tab` ('all', 'active', 'completed'). Crucially, this version includes an artificial 500ms delay using a `while` loop with `performance.now()` to simulate a computationally expensive filtering operation, demonstrating the performance impact when called frequently without memoization.
SOURCE: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/reference/react/useMemo.md#2025-04-22_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
