TITLE: Implementation of a useCounter Hook - React JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet implements a custom useCounter Hook, which provides a counter value that automatically increments every second. It uses the useState and useEffect Hooks from React: useState holds the counter state, and useEffect sets up a setInterval timer and ensures cleanup with clearInterval. The delay is hardcoded at 1000ms and is not configurable. Outputs the current count as a number, and no parameters or special configuration is required. Dependencies are useState and useEffect from React.
SOURCE: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/reusing-logic-with-custom-hooks.md#2025-04-22_snippet_38

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';

export function useCounter() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
  useEffect(() => {
    const id = setInterval(() => {
      setCount(c => c + 1);
    }, 1000);
    return () => clearInterval(id);
  }, []);
  return count;
}
```

