TITLE: Refined Chat Connection Handling with useEffectEvent (JavaScript, Experimental React)
DESCRIPTION: Showcases the use of the experimental useEffectEvent React API to decouple event-driven logic (such as notifications) from resource synchronization (server connection) effects. Ensures that theme changes do not cause unnecessary reconnections, limiting the effect's dependencies only to roomId. Integrates mock connection, UI, and notification logic. Requires the experimental React build and toastify-js for full functionality.
