TITLE: Dispatching Actions in React Event Handlers - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: The JavaScript code snippets provided here illustrate the implementation of dispatch actions triggered by user interactions. These actions are used in the context of a contacts/chat interface in a React application, and rely on a reducer for state updates. The ContactList component triggers a 'changed_selection' action upon button clicks, while the Chat component uses an 'edited_message' action when text changes. The inputs to the reducer must match the expected action object shape, which includes identifiers or messages as needed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/extracting-state-logic-into-a-reducer.md#2025-04-22_snippet_20

