TITLE: Refactoring Animation Logic into a JavaScript Class
DESCRIPTION: This code refactors the fade-in animation logic into a JavaScript class, making it reusable and decoupled from React's Effects. The class manages the animation state internally and offers start and stop methods. Dependencies include a DOM node reference, and it abstracts performance timing and requestAnimationFrame handling.
SOURCE: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/reusing-logic-with-custom-hooks.md#2025-04-22_snippet_33

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import { useState, useEffect, useRef } from 'react';
import { useFadeIn } from './useFadeIn.js';

function Welcome() {
  const ref = useRef(null);

  useFadeIn(ref, 1000);

  return (
    <h1 className="welcome" ref={ref}>
      Welcome
    </h1>
  );
}

export default function App() {
  const [show, setShow] = useState(false);
  return (
    <>
      <button onClick={() => setShow(!show)}>
        {show ? 'Remove' : 'Show'}
      </button>
      <hr />
      {show && <Welcome />}
    </>
  );
